This paper is primarily focused on image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multi-scale features and the structure of the DAG-CNNs, which could potentially fall under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. However, given the focus on image classification and CNNs, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category.
